rson-assessments/"><strong>Responsible Person Assessments</strong><p>New York State may hold you personally liable for your business’ unpaid withholding or sales taxes, regardless of your stake in ownership of the business.  Contact us if you have been assessed as a responsible person by the New York State Department of Taxation and Finance.</p></a></div></li><li><div class="categoryListItems"><a href="<?php echo SITE_URL; ?>/tax-law-nyc-nys-irs/llc-responsible-person-assessment/"><strong>LLC Responsible Person Assessment</strong><p>New York State tax law is particularly strict regarding limited liability companies (LLCs).  Members of an LLC, regardless of level of involvement in a business’ day-to-day affairs, are held personally responsible for unpaid sales taxes.  If this applies to you, you may be eligible for relief under certain circumstances.  Contact us for more information.</p></a></div></li><li><div class="categoryListItems"><a href="<?php echo SITE_URL; ?>/tax-law-nyc-nys-irs/warrants-levies-and-seizures/"><strong>Warrants, Levies, and Seizures</strong><p>As part of collection activity, the New York State Tax Department can impose a levy on your bank account, garnish your wages, and/or seize your property.  Please reach out to us if you are met with this worrisome situation so that we can examine your options.</p></a></div></li><li><div class="categoryListItems"><a href="<?php echo SITE_URL; ?>/tax-law-nyc-nys-irs/installment-payment-agreements/"><strong>Installment Payment Agreements</strong><p>You may be able to pay your outstanding New York State tax liability over time, avoiding levies and garnishments.  Contact us to discuss whether an Installment Payment Agreement (IPA) is the right solution for you.</p></a></div></li><li><div class="categoryListItems"><a href="<?php echo SITE_URL; ?>/tax-law-nyc-nys-irs/ny-offers-in-compromise/"><strong>Offers in Compromise</strong><p>Under the New York State Offer in Compromise program, the State may settle with a taxpayer for less than the full amount due on a tax liability.  We can help you determine whether this process would apply in your specific circumstances.</p></a></div></li><li><div class="categoryListItems"><a href="<?php echo SITE_URL; ?>/tax-law-nyc-nys-irs/drivers-license-suspension/"><strong>Driver’s License Suspension</strong><p>Your New York State driver’s license can be suspended if you owe delinquent taxes.  This is an important reason not to delay in resolving your state tax debt.  Contact our office for a consultation.</p></a></div></li></ul></div>
						
